M|Prin|tx|Survivorship bias occurs when we draw conclusions from winners while ignoring the losers who used the same st. The visible survivors distort our understanding of what actually works.
M|Clas|Duri|armor the areas w/ no damage, bc planes hit there never returned.
M|Deci|tx|Use this md during **Decomposition** (Steps 1-2) and **Challenge** (Steps 5-6) to surface hidden data gaps.
M|Veri|When|
M|Veri|tx|1. What failures used the same approach but are not visible?
M|Veri|tx|2. Are we studying survivors or the full population?
M|Veri|tx|3. What data are we missing bc failures were discarded?
M|Veri|tx|4. Is the sample self-selected (only successes reported)?
M|Red |tx|\| Signal \| Risk \|
M|Red |tx|\|--------\|------\|
M|Red |tx|\| "Company X did this and succeeded" \| Ignoring companies that did the same and failed \|
M|Red |tx|\| "Our successful projects all used pattern Y" \| Failed projects using Y were forgotten \|
M|Red |tx|\| "This approach always works" \| Selection bias in evidence \|
M|Red |tx|\| "Top performers do Z" \| Studying survivors, not the full cohort \|
M|Red |tx|\| "We've never had a problem w/ this" \| Problems were silently discarded or unreported \|
M|Cont|Gene|
M|Cont|it|"How many teams tried this approach and failed? Where is that data?"
M|Cont|it|"Are we looking at the planes that came back, or the ones that didn't?"
M|Cont|it|"Is our evidence base self-selected?"
M|Fail|it|Adopting a st bc visible successes used it, ignoring invisible failures
M|Fail|it|Reinforcing existing patterns bc only their successes are measured
M|Fail|it|Dismissing alternatives bc no visible successes exist (they were never tried)
M|Fail|it|Over-investing in approaches w/ hi visibility but unknown fl rates
M|Prac|Befo|
M|Prac|it|[ ] fl cases examined, not just successes
M|Prac|it|[ ] Sample includes non-survivors (full population)
M|Prac|it|[ ] Selection mechanism for evidence is understood
M|Prac|it|[ ] Base rate of sc/fl is known or estimated
M|Prac|it|[ ] Alternative explanations for observed pattern considered
M|Rela|- Co|seeking evidence that supports existing beliefs
M|Rela|- Ba|ignoring overall probability when evaluating specific cases
M|Rela|- Sy|examining the full sy, not just visible outputs